                        <summary>
                            <p>Dedication of the Atiraṇacaṇdeśvara cave-temple engraved in Grantha alphabet on the right wall (north) before the entrance. Faces the inscription <ref target="DHARMA_INSPallava00064"/> which has almost exactly the same content but in Grantha alphabet.</p>
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p>Miniature <foreign>halanta t</foreign>, <foreign>m</foreign>. The double <foreign>daṇḍa</foreign> is peculiar: the <foreign>daṇḍa</foreign>s are joint in between them on top by a kind of hook. A clear example is found in line 4.</p>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
